
◈ DOTFILES 
Dot • Reference

--- Dotfiles ---
  •    Usage          dot [command]
  •    Version        v0.0.0

  •    What it is                          A single command for setting up, checking, and maintaining this shell environment.
  •    Platforms                           macOS, Linux, and WSL
  •    Start                               Run 'dot sync', then 'dot doctor', then 'dot learn'

== Start Here ==
  •  sync             Apply dotfiles to this machine.
  •  doctor           Check the environment and surface issues.
  •  learn            Open the guided tour.
  •  help             Show the overview or help for one command.

== Daily Use ==
  •  status           Show local drift.
  •  diff             Preview pending changes.
  •  edit             Open the source directory.
  •  upgrade          Update tools and dotfiles.

== Inspect and Repair ==
  •  doctor           Run the main health check.
  •  attest           Export workstation evidence.
  •  rollback         Return to a previous state.
  •  lint             Check shell script quality.

== AI and Agents ==
  •  ai               Show installed AI tools.
  •  mcp              Inspect MCP policy and registry.
  •  mode             Show or set the agent profile.
  •  agent            Show agent metadata, logs, checkpoints, and conformance.

== Fleet ==
  •  fleet            Show fleet node status, drift, and namespace.

== Configuration ==
  •  env              Show managed tool versions.
  •  profile          Show or switch the active profile.
  •  secrets          Edit or manage encrypted secrets.
  •  theme            Switch the terminal theme.

== Reference ==
  •  search           Find commands by keyword.
  •  help all         Show the full command reference.
  •  version          Show version information.

  •    Next                                Run 'dot help all' for the full command list
  •    Detail                              Run 'dot help <command>' for one command
